cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with formal verification of timed systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science. The use of automata and decidability results suggest that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category. The addition of parameters and the study of their impact on decidability suggest cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of clocks and the study of complexity suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the focus on timed systems and interruptions suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control).
